<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I have not seen this addressed before on this board, and I don't know if it's just me, or if others have had this problem.<P>When fighting outside, I am so far away from the pull that I've got lots of time to target. That's a darn good thing, because it very often takes me two or three clicks to target that incoming mob.<P>When in a dungeon however, mobs are coming around a corner typically, and I've got a very short period of time to pick a target. It is so incredibly frustrating to click three times on an incoming mob and get NO TARGET.<P>I'm guessing it's a problem with client-side prediction or something, perhaps the mob isn't *really* in the position my client thinks it's in. Whatever the cause, if I can't target the mob as it's running towards me, I very often die a quick death - those extra seconds make all the difference in a big pull.<P>I run on a cable modem in Southern California, and usually seem to have a pretty good connection to the servers, although with the useless lag meter, it's impossible to tell what sort of connection I've really got.<P>Anybody else have this problem? I swear if I could get those guys targeted as they come, I'd be so much more effective.<P>And yes, I know that this is not a sorc specific problem (if indeed it is a problem at all). But it has impacted me to the point that I have wanted to quit many times as I watch my group die while I lie dead and helpless on the floor next to them.<P>For some background, I have LOTS of experience doing crowd control. I was a very effective enchanter in EQ (lvl 54), and I know that picking targets quickly is one of the most important things we need to be able to do.<P>--------------------<P>Naeen / 46 Sorc / Morgan Le Fay<BR>See my sorc guide at  <A HREF="http://www.hallowedcrusaders.org" TARGET=_blank>http://www.hallowedcrusaders.org</A>  (see Articles)
