<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've never had a problem with this Naeen, wasn't aware others were either. Here's what works for me..<P>If your fighting in a dungeon, will use barrows as an example simply because i'm there right now and it's easier to visualize,, you want to put yourself in one of two ideal hunting situations.<P> First, fight amid the spawns that are being pulled, or close enough that you can see them without having to keep getting up and moving around between pulls, and coordinate a system with yor puller so that he/she is pulling one that you "don't" have targeted, and you have your first mez already done by the time they pull. This works extraordinarily well with fallen warriors, if you can time around a merc scout or armsperson shooting a bow, you can have the first add mezzed almost immediately, and plenty of time to target the second(and third and so on if your being really daring). <P>Second, find a room or area to pull from that gives you visiblity of the entry to said area and a bit beyond, and have your group fight to one side of it. This will allow you a clear field of view and usually enough time to target before it can start beating on someone or come charge you. Works exceptionally well with delayed multipulls, such as usually happens with megalith wights(I apologize if the barrows references are meaningless, you will see as you adventure further in =). <P>I know that doesn't necessarily adress the technical aspect of it, but I hope that helps for at least putting yourself in a good position to counter it,, I've not had any problems at all even in cramped quarters. One thing i do if i'm feeling lazy or just frustrated with clicking is cycling through f8, it's not always reliable, but i've found at least 9 times out of 10, that if theres a multiple pull and your puller/party is already engaging one, cycling through f8 twice will give you the next target based on proximity, so even though by the time you get your mez off it will be right in your face, you can usually have the correct one targeted.<P>Hope that helped somewhat, and good luck in your dungeon romps.<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Enigmatic of 41 seasons on Percival<BR>Proud member of The Dawn's Chosen<P>--------------------<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Sorceress of 45 seasons on Percival<BR>Proud Member of The Dawn's Chosen
