<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
In Barrows there a few spots you have to get a slightly higher position before AE mez will actually work.  AE Mez will hit the target, but not things around it.  Even though you can single target and have LOS for each NPC in the radius of the spell.  If you move to a slightly higher position, then you can ae mez everything fine.  The worse spot I can think of for this is down at the Barrow wights/Celtic Lichs.<P>As far as other targeting I don't have too many problems.  Clicking and/or hitting nearest NPC pretty much always for me.  Knowing which target to select is a big part of the skill required to be a sorc.  Some targeting issues I believe are related to the system you play on.  I run on a fast system at 1280X1024 and target fairly easily.  Getting the 'target not in view' is a common problem though.<P>Ierar
</FONT>
