Yet ANOTHER Percival sorceress logs on to post for the first time... (waves at everyone)<P>I have to agree with the above posters that position is everything. In the sorc-favorite Fallen Warriors room, I always make sure the pally running the heal chant has me on protect, just to ensure that I will not be randomly selected in a group pull.<P>I try and stand just at the edge of his protect range, and well away from the kill box. If I mez a target that then turns to look at me, I make sure I am well away from it before the other players break the mez.<P>I also try to make sure that the healers stand relatively close to me, so that an f8 has a better chance of selecting the occasional mob that aggros on the healers.<P>Formia Greengale<BR>Level 35 Sorc<BR>Percival - Albion
</FONT>
